/span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 18th 10:26 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello all! I have been wanting to try a bard for quite a while and what I have been dying to know is what good starting stats are. I currently have a Lvl 7 Wood Elf Bard with these stats:<br>STR: 90<br>STA: 65<br>AGI: 95<br>DEX: 90<br>WIS: 80<br>INT: 75<br>CHA: 90<br><br>So +20 STR and +5 CHA. The only Bard creation guide I have seen is on Casters Realm but there is no information as to why they suggest those stats. I understand CHA for charming but why DEX? From all the descriptions I have ever seen it helps with procs and the ability to hit a target.<br><br>I did find one post on another site where someone was saying that they deeply regretted having put most of their points into STR.<br><br>Should I reroll while i'm only level 7? Are my current stats going to be something i'll regret later on? I thought that +STR would be beneficial for later plate armor wearing and such. I know that a Half Elf might have better stats for a bard but I still think i'd prefer a Wood Elf.<br><br>Please help! Thank you!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100092036618728></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100092036618728><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100092036618728>RE: Newbie Bard Starting Race/Stats?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100092036618728#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85052><span id= >Bakra</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>50 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 19th 1:26 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i think you are pretty well balanced. Though that 65 sta could hurt if you are using heavy weapons, you are still ok since bards don't HAVE to use weapons later on. You will need to raise dex, that determines how well you play your instruments so that you don't miss notes, but you can get items to raise that up, no need to recreate yourself.<br> I play a half-elf, his base stats are:<br>80 str<br>75 sta<br>95 agi<br>100 dex<br>60 wis<br>75 int<br>90 cha<br> And with my equipment it is:<br>88 str<br>75 sta<br>95 agi<br>104 dex<br>60 wis<br>75 int<br>95 cha<br><br>So i think you did good=)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
